    "comment": "Rationale: Fig2: APLP2 colocalises with dendritic marker MAP2 in primary cortical neurons; the colocalisation was abolished in APLP2 KO neurons indicating the specificity of the staining towards APLP2.\nFig4B: The endogenous localisation of APLP2 was difficult to discern due to the quality of the signal derived by the antibody. The paper used HA-tagged APLP2 and GFP to visualize the dendritic spines. Staining with anti-HA antibody revealed partial colocalisation with APLP2 in the head, neck, or at the bottom of dendritic spines.. Experimental description: C57BL/6J mice were used for the generation of primary cortical neuron cultures. The generation and genotyping of APLP2 KO was described in von Koch et al., 1997.",
